The CSS Box model defines how elements are displayed on the page and how they are sized.  All elements on a
webpage can be located in a rectangular container which has:
1.  Content -> specify height and width.
2.  Border -> inside the rectangular container.
3.  Padding -> spacing within the box, between the content and the border.
4.  Margin -> spacing outside the box, between the border and the next element, with two adjacent elements we
only have to specify the margin for one of the elements, the collapsing margin rule will chose the larger
spacing between two adjacent elements with overlapping margins.
5.  Fill Area -> Content, padding, and border.  Background color fills all three.
6.  Final width of element = left border + left padding + element width + right padding + right border
7.  Final height of element = lower border + lower padding + element height + top padding + top border

